Recommends: pkexec | policykit-1
Description: Linux client for PDA Net WiFi Direct Hotspot
 PDAnet-linux shares your phone's cellular data connection
 with a Linux machine by managing the HTTP proxy that PDA Net's
 "WiFi Direct Hotspot" mode exposes on the phone.
 .
 Includes:
  - pdanet CLI: on/off/status/test/watch commands
  - pdanet-gui: libadwaita GUI with live traffic monitor and speed test
 .
 Supports bash, zsh, fish, tcsh, ksh, and dash out of the box.
